CAE Test Framework
==================

This directory contains the CAE (Cycle Approximate Engine) test suite,
organized by architecture following the same structure as tests/tcg/.

Directory Structure
-------------------

    tests/cae/
    ├── Makefile.target              Main orchestrator
    ├── README                       This file
    ├── multiarch/                   Architecture-agnostic tests
    │   ├── system/                  Shared system-mode tests
    │   └── difftest/                Shared difftest utilities
    └── riscv64/                     RISC-V 64-bit tests
        ├── Makefile.target          User-mode tests
        ├── Makefile.softmmu-target  System-mode tests
        ├── Makefile.difftest-target Difftest targets (CAE vs gem5)
        ├── system/                  System test sources and scripts
        └── difftest/                Difftest infrastructure
            ├── benchmarks/          Tier-1 microbenchmarks + MANIFEST
            ├── configs/             Paired YAML configurations
            ├── scripts/             Python/Bash drivers
            └── reports/             Output artifacts (git-ignored)

Test Modes
----------

Each architecture directory can provide three Makefiles:

  Makefile.target
    User-mode tests. Run under qemu-<arch> (linux-user) with CAE
    instrumentation hooks. Tests instruction classification and basic
    UOP metadata without a full machine model.

  Makefile.softmmu-target
    System-mode tests. Run under qemu-system-<arch> -accel cae. Tests
    the full CAE timing path including one-insn-per-tb charging, branch
    prediction, cache modeling, and event queue mechanics.

  Makefile.difftest-target
    Difftest mode (specialization of system-mode). Runs paired
    comparisons between CAE and a reference simulator (gem5 for
    in-order, XiangShan GEM5 for OoO) using identical configurations
    (paired YAML). Reports IPC, cycle count, misprediction rate, and
    other metrics. Used for accuracy calibration.

Quick Start
-----------

    # Build and run in-order difftest suite (RISC-V 64)
    make -C tests/cae/riscv64 -f ../Makefile.target build-difftest
    make -C tests/cae/riscv64 -f ../Makefile.target run-difftest

    # Run a single benchmark
    make -C tests/cae/riscv64 -f ../Makefile.target \
        run-difftest-single CONFIG=inorder-1c BENCH=alu

    # Unit tests (via meson, arch-independent)
    meson test -C build-cae qemu:test-cae --print-errorlogs

Adding a New Architecture
-------------------------

1. Create tests/cae/<arch>/
2. Add Makefile.target for user-mode tests
3. Add Makefile.softmmu-target for system-mode tests
4. Optionally add Makefile.difftest-target with reference sim configs
5. Add benchmark sources under <arch>/difftest/benchmarks/src/
